itemDescription: Principal of Jesus College, Oxford from 1720 to 1725

wikipedia_page.main: William Jones (26 February 1676 – 29 November 1725), born Kidwelly, Wales, was Principal of Jesus College, Oxford, from 1720 to 1725.  He had previously been a student of the college, obtaining his BA in 1697, his MA in 1700, his BD in 1708 and his DD in 1720.
